<p>The regular way to change programmatically menu item icon is save reference to the menu after onCreateOptionsMenu() called:</p>  <pre><code>private Menu mOptionsMenu; @Override public boolean onCreateOptionsMenu(Menu menu) {     mOptionsMenu = menu;     getMenuInflater().inflate(R.menu.menu_main, menu);     return true; } </code></pre>  <p>and then access it like: <code>mOptionsMenu.findItem(R.id.action_something).setIcon(R.mipmap.new_icon);</code></p>  <p>My question is how to set new icon before onCreateOptionsMenu() called - so I don't have reference to the menu?</p>  <p>Thanks,</p>